article.headline: Dartmouth beats Maine 79-69
article.story: BANGOR, Maine -- Evan Boudreaux posted a double-double, scoring 18 points with 13 rebounds, as Dartmouth beat Maine 79-69 on Wednesday night. Boudreaux finished with 5-of-10 shooting from the field and 8-of-8 from the line for the Big Green (3-3). Miles Wright added 19 points and four rebounds and Connor Boehm had 14 points and five rebounds. Dartmouth won it with superior shooting, averaging 49.1 percent from the field, 73.1 percent from the line and hitting 6 of 15 (40 percent) from beyond the arc. Maine averaged 40.8 percent from the field, 60 percent from the line and made just 5 of 29 (17.2 percent) from distance. The Big Green had a 42-33 advantage at the break and held on in the second half for the win. Ryan Bernstein scored 13 points with eight assists and six rebounds or the Black Bears (2-6). Lavar Harewood added 12 points and four rebounds.
